Action.name: FlipIncrementalLeft
Action.description: Incrementally rotate the targets counter-clockwise around their flip axes, typically the scene's Z-axis.

Action.name: FlipIncrementalRight
Action.description: Incrementally rotate the targets clockwise around their flip axes, typically the scene's Z-axis.

Action.name: FlipOver
Action.description: Rotate the targets 180 degrees around their flip axes, typically the scene's Z-axis i.e. toggle the targets between face up and face down.

Action.name: RotateIncrementalLeft
Action.description: Rotate the targets incrementally, typically counter-clockwise around the scene's Y-axis. Instead of being rotated exclusively around the Y-axis, dice will be rotated to the previous rotation value.

Action.name: RotateIncrementalRight
Action.description: Rotate the targets incrementally, typically clockwise around the scene's Y-axis. Instead of being rotated exclusively around the Y-axis, dice will be rotated to the next rotation value.

Action.name: RotateOver
Action.description: Rotate the targets 180 degrees around the scene's Y-axis.

Action.name: Select
Action.description: Add the targets to the player's selection.

Action.name: Under
Action.description: Move the targets underneath objects below them on table.

math.name: tan
math.description: Returns the tangent of x (assumed to be in radians).

math.name: tanh
math.description: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of x.

string.description: Returns the substring of s that starts at i and continues until j.

string.description: Returns the unicode numerical codes of the characters s[i], s[i+1], ..., s[j].

string.name: upper
string.description: Returns the string converted to upper case.

table.name: concat
table.description: Returns a string of items i to j in list joined by sep.

table.name: insert
table.description: Inserts element value at position pos in list.

table.name: pack
table.description: Returns a new table with all parameters stored into keys 1, 2, etc. and with a field "n" with the total number of parameters.

table.name: remove
table.description: Removes (and returns) item pos from list.

table.name: sort
table.description: Sorts list in place. Uses compare function comp if specified.

table.name: unpack
table.description: Returns elemeents i to j from list.

Tables.name: getCustomURL
Tables.description: Returns the image URL of the current Custom Table, or nil if the current table is not a Custom Table.

Tables.name: getTable
Tables.description: Returns the current Table's name i.e. equivalent to getTableObject().name.

Tables.name: setCustomURL
Tables.description: Sets the image URL for the current Custom Table. Has no effect if the current Table is not a Custom Table.

Tables.name: setTable
Tables.description: Replaces the current Table with the Table matching the specified name.

TextTool.name: getFontColor
TextTool.description: Returns the current font color as a Lua table keyed as table["r"], table["g"], and table["b"].

TextTool.name: setFontColor
TextTool.description: Sets the current font color. The Lua table parameter should be keyed as table["r"], table["g"], and table["b"].

Time.name: time
Time.description: The current game time in seconds.

Time.name: delta_time
Time.description: Time in seconds since the last frame.

Time.name: fixed_time
Time.description: The game time of the last fixedUpdate.

Time.name: fixed_delta_time
Time.description: Duration of fixed update in seconds.

Time.name: frame_count
Time.description: Total number of frames since the scene began.

Turns.name: type
Turns.description: If the turn order is automatic or custom. 1=auto, 2=custom.

Turns.name: order
Turns.description: A table of strings, representing the player turn order.

Turns.name: disable_interactations
Turns.description: Enable/disable the blocking of players ability to interact with Objects when it is not their turn.

Turns.name: pass_turns
Turns.description: Enable/disable a player's ability to pass their turn to another.

Turns.name: turn_color
Turns.description: The color of the Player who's turn it is.

Turns.name: getNextTurnColor
Turns.description: Returns the Player Color string of the next player in the turn order.

Turns.name: getPreviousTurnColor
Turns.description: Returns the Player Color string of the previous player in the turn order.

UI.name: loading
UI.description: Is true if the UI is still loading on this object.

UI.name: getAttribute
UI.description: Obtains the value of a specified attribute of a UI element. Returns typically a string or number.

UI.name: getAttributes
UI.description: Returns the attributes and their values of a UI element that have been set by the user.

UI.name: getValue
UI.description: Gets the value of a UI element.

UI.name: setAttribute
UI.description: Sets the value of a specified attribute of a UI element.

UI.name: setAttributes
UI.description: Updates the value of the supplied attributes of a UI element.

UI.name: setValue
UI.description: Updates the value of a UI element.

UI.name: setXml
UI.description: Replaces the run-time UI with the XML string.

UI.name: setXmlTable
UI.description: Replaces the run-time UI with an XML string which is generated from a table of data.

UI.name: setCustomAssets
UI.description: Sets the UI ASSETS (like custom images) for global or an Object.

UI.name: getXml
UI.description: Returns the run-time UI's XML in string format.

UI.name: getXmlTable
UI.description: Returns the run-time UI's XML formatted as a Lua table.

UI.name: getCustomAssets
UI.description: Returns information on all custom assets uploaded to the UI ASSETS pane.

Vector.name: max
Vector.description: Returns a new Vector with the max component of each parameter.

Vector.name: min
Vector.description: Returns a new Vector with the min component of each parameter.

Vector.name: between
Vector.description: Returns a new Vector pointing from v1 to v2.

Wait.name: condition
Wait.description: Activates a function when a given function returns true or activates a different function if a timeout occurs.

Wait.name: frames
Wait.description: Activates a function after a set number of frames.

Wait.name: stop
Wait.description: Stops a currently running Wait function.

Wait.name: time
Wait.description: Activates a function after a set amount of time has passed, repeats given amount of times.

WebRequest.name: custom
WebRequest.description: Performs a HTTP request using the specified method, data and headers.

WebRequest.name: get
WebRequest.description: Get data in text from the url. Callback function is supplied the WebRequest.

WebRequest.name: post
WebRequest.description: Post the form to the url. Callback function is supplied the WebRequest.

WebRequest.name: put
WebRequest.description: Put the data to the url. Callback function is supplied the WebRequest.
